237
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:35,823
- l'm telling you now.
- Great. Thank you.

238
00:20:38,473 --> 00:20:41,073
Willow, it's Anya. How could you let us...

239
00:20:41,553 --> 00:20:43,603
How could you not have told us?

240
00:20:44,713 --> 00:20:47,153
- Xander...
- How could you not have told me?

241
00:20:47,153 --> 00:20:48,453
Xander. lt's OK.

242
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:52,333
She didn't tell us for a reason.

243
00:20:53,913 --> 00:20:57,113
She didn't tell us
because she knows what l have to do.

244
00:20:59,953 --> 00:21:01,453
l have to kill Anya.

245
00:21:07,953 --> 00:21:09,553
<i>(woman giggles)</i>

246
00:21:13,873 --> 00:21:15,673
l swear l'm in awe of you.

247
00:21:16,833 --> 00:21:18,733
- Oh, stop.
- Oh, l will not.

248
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:23,933
l grant wishes. lt's all inside the girl.
l just... bring it out.

249
00:21:24,673 --> 00:21:28,673
- Yes. l'm sure this is what she had in mind.
- <i>(cannons firing)</i>

250
00:21:28,753 --> 00:21:32,153
Well, l don't know about her mind,
but it was in her heart.

251
00:21:32,353 --> 00:21:36,033
Besides, Russia was ready to explode.
We just gave it a little push.

252
00:21:36,033 --> 00:21:40,033
What should we do now? l hear
they're going to raze the Winter Mansion.

253
00:21:40,553 --> 00:21:45,203
We could head down to Madame Dubasov's.
No better spot for vengeance than a brothel.

254
00:21:45,233 --> 00:21:47,633
lt's always work, work, work with you.

255
00:21:48,793 --> 00:21:50,873
- What else is there?
<i>- (man screaming)</i>

256
00:21:50,873 --> 00:21:53,823
What else is there?
Why, the whole world, for one.

257
00:21:54,033 --> 00:21:56,983
Darling, take a look around.
There's a lot to see.

258
00:21:57,033 --> 00:22:01,283
There's a revolution going on outside
that you are somewhat responsible for.

259
00:22:01,513 --> 00:22:03,963
Aren't you the teeniest bit interested?

260
00:22:04,193 --> 00:22:08,073
What is there to be interested in?
The worker will overthrow absolutism

261
00:22:08,073 --> 00:22:11,433
and lead the proletariat
to a victorious communist revolution,

262
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:15,533
resulting in socio-economic paradise
on earth. lt's common sense, really.

263
00:22:15,913 --> 00:22:18,213
l have better things to worry about.

264
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:20,533
But there's a whole world out there.

265
00:22:20,753 --> 00:22:23,433
Yes. Filled with wronged women
who need my help.

266
00:22:23,433 --> 00:22:26,583
- You're talking about work.
- l'm talking about life.

267
00:22:26,673 --> 00:22:30,123
Vengeance is what l do, Halfrek.
l don't need anything else.

268
00:22:32,193 --> 00:22:33,843
Vengeance is what l am.

269
00:22:35,673 --> 00:22:38,633
She's not the Anya you knew, Xander.
She's a demon.

270
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:42,633
- That doesn't mean you have to kill her.
- Don't act like this is easy for me.

271
00:22:42,633 --> 00:22:45,433
- You know it's not.
- There are other options.

272
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:47,623
l've considered them.

273
00:22:47,953 --> 00:22:49,203
When? Just now?

274
00:22:50,033 --> 00:22:53,833
Took you all of ten seconds to decide
to kill one of your best friends?

275
00:22:53,833 --> 00:22:57,533
The thought that it might come to this
has occurred to me before.

276
00:22:57,833 --> 00:22:59,633
lt's occurred to you, too.

277
00:22:59,913 --> 00:23:02,363
But we can change what she did. Fix it.

278
00:23:03,513 --> 00:23:06,513
These are mystical deaths.
There has to be something.

279
00:23:06,513 --> 00:23:10,913
l don't have anywhere near that power.
l didn't have that kind of power when...

280
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:14,753
And l don't think l trust the power l do have.

281
00:23:14,873 --> 00:23:15,773
lt's OK.

282
00:23:17,433 --> 00:23:21,483
Xander, l know this is hard for you to hear,
but it's what l have to do.

283
00:23:22,953 --> 00:23:25,803
Hard for me to hear?
Buffy, you wanna kill Anya!

284
00:23:26,313 --> 00:23:28,363
- l don't want to.
- Then don't!

285
00:23:28,553 --> 00:23:33,403
This isn't new ground. When our friends go
crazy and start killing people, we help them.

286
00:23:33,513 --> 00:23:35,663
- Sitting right here.
- l'm sorry.

287
00:23:35,913 --> 00:23:37,993
- But it's true.
- lt's different.

288
00:23:37,993 --> 00:23:40,993
Because you don't care about her
the same way l do.

289
00:23:41,793 --> 00:23:44,043
- Buffy, l still love her.
- l know.

290
00:23:46,113 --> 00:23:49,363
And that's why you can't see this
for what it really is.

291
00:23:49,753 --> 00:23:52,053
Willow was different. She's a human.

292
00:23:52,913 --> 00:23:55,463
- Anya's a demon.
- And you're the Slayer.

293
00:23:57,713 --> 00:23:59,963
l see now how it's all very simple.

294
00:24:00,753 --> 00:24:02,203
lt is never simple.

295
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,233
No, of course not.

296
00:24:05,713 --> 00:24:06,663
You know,

297
00:24:07,153 --> 00:24:12,003
if there's a mass-murdering demon that
you're, oh, say, boning, then it's all grey area.

298
00:24:12,233 --> 00:24:15,533
- Spike was harmless. He was helping.
- He had no choice.

299
00:24:15,753 --> 00:24:18,703
And Anya did!
She chose to become a demon - twice.

300
00:24:20,233 --> 00:24:23,683
- You have no idea what she's going through.
- l don't care!

301
00:24:23,833 --> 00:24:27,333
No, of course not.
You think we haven't all seen this before?

302
00:24:27,393 --> 00:24:29,473
The part where you cut us all out.

303
00:24:29,473 --> 00:24:33,173
Just step away from everything human
and act like you're the law.

304
00:24:33,193 --> 00:24:35,943
- lf you knew what l felt...
- l killed Angel.

305
00:24:39,593 --> 00:24:41,393
Do you even remember that?

306
00:24:42,553 --> 00:24:45,603
l would have given up
everything l had to be with...

307
00:24:47,593 --> 00:24:51,093
l loved him more than
l will ever love anything in this life.

308
00:24:52,113 --> 00:24:55,213
And l put a sword through his heart
because l had to.

309
00:24:56,153 --> 00:24:58,003
And that all worked out OK.

310
00:24:58,833 --> 00:25:01,483
Do you remember cheering me on?
Both of you.

311
00:25:03,353 --> 00:25:06,403
Remember giving me Willow's message:
"Kick his ass"?

312
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:08,873
- l never said that!
- This is different.

313
00:25:08,873 --> 00:25:11,773
lt is always different! lt's always complicated.

314
00:25:13,193 --> 00:25:17,743
And at some point someone has to draw
the line, and that is always going to be me.

315
00:25:18,953 --> 00:25:23,753
You get down on me for cutting myself off,
but in the end the Slayer is always cut off.

316
00:25:25,833 --> 00:25:28,983
There's no mystical guidebook.
No all-knowing council.

317
00:25:29,793 --> 00:25:31,493
Human rules don't apply.

318
00:25:33,353 --> 00:25:34,653
There's only me.

319
00:25:35,713 --> 00:25:36,863
l am the law.

320
00:25:40,353 --> 00:25:43,453
- There has to be another way.
- Then please find it.

321
00:26:09,153 --> 00:26:10,603
l can't. l'm sorry.

322
00:26:33,553 --> 00:26:36,053
<i>Beatum sit in nomine D'Hoffrynis.</i>

323
00:26:43,433 --> 00:26:45,233
<i>Fiat hoc spatium...</i>

324
00:26:45,913 --> 00:26:47,663
<i>porta ad mundum...</i>

325
00:26:48,633 --> 00:26:50,133
<i>Arashmaharis.</i>

326
00:26:54,353 --> 00:26:56,753
Behold, D'Hoffryn. Lord of Arashmahar.

327
00:26:57,833 --> 00:27:00,483
He that turns the air to blood and rains...

328
00:27:01,793 --> 00:27:03,043
Miss Rosenberg.

329
00:27:03,673 --> 00:27:07,523
How lovely to see you again.
Have you done something with your hair?

330
00:27:07,713 --> 00:27:11,213
- Hello, D'Hoffryn.
- l figured l'd be hearing from you soon.

331
00:27:11,473 --> 00:27:14,123
The flaying of Warren Meers?
Truly inspired.

332
00:27:15,353 --> 00:27:19,303
That was water-cooler vengeance.
Lloyd has a sketch of it on his wall.

333
00:27:19,753 --> 00:27:22,303
- That's not me any more.
- ls that right?

334
00:27:23,313 --> 00:27:26,113
So, l didn't feel your presence earlier today?

335
00:27:26,793 --> 00:27:29,043
l didn't feel a bit of the old you?

336
00:27:29,953 --> 00:27:31,803
We need to talk about Anya.

337
00:27:32,553 --> 00:27:33,803
<i>(groans)</i>

338
00:27:35,433 --> 00:27:37,733
Very well. Let's talk about Anyanka.

339
00:27:45,353 --> 00:27:49,403
- <i>(door opens)</i>
- <i>(Xander)</i> l thought l might find you here.

340
00:27:49,673 --> 00:27:52,673
Have you forced yourself
to look at the bodies yet?

341
00:27:52,833 --> 00:27:55,233
- What do you want?
- l wanna help you.

342
00:27:56,153 --> 00:28:00,353
Everyone is so considerate today.
l should've slaughtered people weeks ago.

343
00:28:02,473 --> 00:28:06,873
l'm sorry. l'm sorry for everything
l did to you, everything l put you through.

344
00:28:07,113 --> 00:28:10,613
Thank you. All better!
Thank goodness you got here in time(!)

345
00:28:11,193 --> 00:28:15,493
You don't understand. This isn't
an intervention. Buffy's coming to kill you.

346
00:28:17,593 --> 00:28:21,153
- She's coming to try.
- Did everyone have their crazy flakes today?

347
00:28:21,153 --> 00:28:26,003
- You're friends. How could you talk like this?
- l have a job to do. And so does Buffy.

348
00:28:26,993 --> 00:28:29,743
Xander, you've always seen
what you wanted to.

349
00:28:30,673 --> 00:28:33,773
But she knew, sooner or later,
it would come to this.

350
00:28:36,673 --> 00:28:39,753
- Buffy, get out of here.
- Get out of my way, Xander.

351
00:28:39,753 --> 00:28:41,953
- No.
- Get out of her way, Xander.

352
00:28:47,313 --> 00:28:52,513
This is getting to be a pattern. Are there any
friends of yours left you haven't tried to kill?

353
00:28:59,953 --> 00:29:03,103
Come on, Buffy.
Don't you have a clever retort for me?

354
00:29:32,473 --> 00:29:35,223
- Anya, l'm sorry.
- You're apologising to me?

355
00:29:37,033 --> 00:29:39,283
What fight are <i>you</i> watching?

356
00:29:39,753 --> 00:29:44,603
Or is this one of your little pop-culture
references l don't get, cos l'm a vengeance...

357
00:29:58,753 --> 00:30:00,403
l just want... happy...

358
00:30:02,913 --> 00:30:03,763
ending.

359
00:30:05,953 --> 00:30:06,753
Honey?

360
00:30:08,113 --> 00:30:09,413
- Honey?
- Wha...

361
00:30:09,953 --> 00:30:11,353
l'm awake. l'm OK.

362
00:30:14,113 --> 00:30:15,713
Honey, was that weird?

363
00:30:17,833 --> 00:30:20,133
That thing earlier with the singing.

364
00:30:21,753 --> 00:30:23,353
- The coconuts.
- What?

365
00:30:25,033 --> 00:30:26,233
No. lt's fine.

366
00:30:27,833 --> 00:30:30,433
<i>(man) #</i> Oh, no! Mustard on my shirt

367
00:30:30,833 --> 00:30:32,583
<i>(woman) #</i> Mustard!

368
00:30:33,033 --> 00:30:35,833
- <i>#</i> l'll never get it out
- <i>#</i> My favourite dress shirt

369
00:30:35,833 --> 00:30:38,433
- <i>#</i> Dry-clean it
- <i>#</i> How could you serve...

370
00:30:38,433 --> 00:30:40,083
<i># (both)</i> Mustard

371
00:30:41,153 --> 00:30:43,603
Are you still hungry? Because l'd be...

372
00:30:49,793 --> 00:30:51,543
<i>#</i> Mr Xander Harris

373
00:30:52,273 --> 00:30:54,753
<i>#</i> That's what he is to the world outside

374
00:30:54,753 --> 00:30:57,553
<i>#</i> That's the name he carries with pride

375
00:30:59,553 --> 00:31:01,503
<i>#</i> l'm just lately Anya

376
00:31:01,913 --> 00:31:04,353
<i>#</i> Not very much to the world, l know

377
00:31:04,353 --> 00:31:07,103
<i>#</i> All these years with nothing to show

378
00:31:08,873 --> 00:31:11,433
<i>#</i> l've boned a troll, l've wreaked some wrath

379
00:31:11,433 --> 00:31:13,833
<i>#</i> But on the whole, l've had no path

380
00:31:13,833 --> 00:31:16,073
<i>#</i> l like to bowl, l'm good with math

381
00:31:16,073 --> 00:31:17,673
<i>#</i> But who am l?

382
00:31:18,433 --> 00:31:20,183
<i>#</i> Now l reply that

383
00:31:21,673 --> 00:31:23,323
<i>#</i> l'm the missis

384
00:31:26,473 --> 00:31:28,423
<i>#</i> l will be his missis

385
00:31:30,673 --> 00:31:33,773
<i>#</i> Mrs Anya Christina Emmanuella
Jenkins Harris

386
00:31:41,433 --> 00:31:43,733
<i>#</i> What's the point of loving?

387
00:31:43,833 --> 00:31:46,113
<i>#</i> l mean, except for the sweaty part

388
00:31:46,113 --> 00:31:48,963
<i>#</i> What's the point of losing your heart?

389
00:31:51,273 --> 00:31:53,273
<i>#</i> Maybe if you're lucky

390
00:31:53,353 --> 00:31:55,713
<i>#</i> Being a pair makes you twice as tall

391
00:31:55,713 --> 00:31:58,163
<i>#</i> Maybe you're not losing at all

392
00:32:00,353 --> 00:32:02,633
<i>#</i> No need to cover up my heart

393
00:32:02,633 --> 00:32:05,083
<i>#</i> Plus see above re: sweaty part

394
00:32:05,193 --> 00:32:07,273
<i>#</i> So maybe love is pretty smart

395
00:32:07,273 --> 00:32:08,823
<i>#</i> Then so am l

396
00:32:09,513 --> 00:32:11,163
<i>#</i> l found my guy

397
00:32:12,673 --> 00:32:14,373
<i>#</i> And l'll be Mrs

398
00:32:17,713 --> 00:32:19,663
<i>#</i> l will be his missis

399
00:32:21,873 --> 00:32:24,973
<i>#</i> Mrs Anya Lame-Ass
Made-up Maiden Name Harris

400
00:32:28,233 --> 00:32:29,983
<i>#</i> We'll never part

401
00:32:30,473 --> 00:32:32,073
<i>#</i> Not if we can

402
00:32:32,953 --> 00:32:34,653
<i>#</i> And if we start

403
00:32:35,353 --> 00:32:37,253
<i>#</i> Then here's my plan

404
00:32:37,433 --> 00:32:39,733
<i>#</i> l'll show him what bliss is

405
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:41,933
<i>#</i> Welcome him with kisses

406
00:32:42,073 --> 00:32:44,823
<i>#</i> Cos this is a Mrs who misses her man

407
00:32:45,953 --> 00:32:48,753
<i>#</i> He's my Xander and he's awfully swell

408
00:32:48,913 --> 00:32:51,233
<i>#</i> And makes financial sense as well

409
00:32:51,233 --> 00:32:53,593
<i>#</i> Although he can be... l'll never tell

410
00:32:53,593 --> 00:32:55,343
<i>#</i> Just stand aside

411
00:32:55,953 --> 00:32:57,903
<i>#</i> Here comes the bride

412
00:32:59,433 --> 00:33:00,933
<i>#</i> l'll be Mrs

413
00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:06,223
<i>#</i> l will be his missis

414
00:33:08,633 --> 00:33:10,183
<i>#</i> l will be...

415
00:33:18,593 --> 00:33:19,343
Anya!

416
00:33:34,913 --> 00:33:37,813
Forgotten how much
swords through the chest hurt.

417
00:33:38,433 --> 00:33:39,283
Aarghh!

418
00:33:47,273 --> 00:33:49,423
You know better than that, Buffy.

419
00:33:50,633 --> 00:33:53,233
lt takes a lot more to kill a vengeance demon.

420
00:33:53,233 --> 00:33:55,183
Oh, l'm just getting started.

421
00:34:15,193 --> 00:34:17,243
Stop trying to save me, Xander!

422
00:34:23,593 --> 00:34:27,443
Please, don't mind me. Continue
with whatever it was you were doing.

423
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:33,503
Oh! Breathtaking.

424
00:34:35,433 --> 00:34:39,083
lt's like somebody slaughtered
an Abercrombie & Fitch catalogue.

425
00:34:39,273 --> 00:34:42,023
Easy, now.
l'd be gone before you could swing.

426
00:34:44,953 --> 00:34:46,903
lsn't thatjust like a slayer?

427
00:34:47,513 --> 00:34:51,113
Solving all her problems
by sticking things with sharp objects.

428
00:34:53,673 --> 00:34:57,023
l talked to your friend Miss Rosenberg.
She's a firebrand.

429
00:34:57,993 --> 00:35:01,093
- l have high hopes for her.
- Stay away from Willow.

430
00:35:01,353 --> 00:35:03,203
Oh, he's gallant, isn't he?

431
00:35:03,433 --> 00:35:05,583
l understand what you saw in him.

432
00:35:06,433 --> 00:35:10,883
Miss Rosenberg thinks Anyanka would be
better suited outside the vengeance fold.

433
00:35:11,513 --> 00:35:14,613
l think we already know
what Lady "Hacks-Away" wants.

434
00:35:14,673 --> 00:35:17,773
And the young man,
he sees with the eyeballs of love.

435
00:35:18,593 --> 00:35:23,243
But l'm not sure if anyone's bothered
to find out what Anyanka herself really wants.

436
00:35:23,753 --> 00:35:27,053
- Her name is Anya.
- Actually, funny historical sidebar:

437
00:35:27,513 --> 00:35:31,163
- her original name was...
- <i>(Anya)</i> l wanna take it back.

438
00:35:31,873 --> 00:35:33,623
l'm sorry. What was that?

439
00:35:35,593 --> 00:35:37,143
l wanna take it back.

440
00:35:39,673 --> 00:35:41,373
l wanna undo what l did.

441
00:35:43,073 --> 00:35:45,073
Hmm. You want to take it back.

442
00:35:47,353 --> 00:35:50,803
Must be 12 bodies in there.
Such a thing... not easily done.

443
00:35:53,513 --> 00:35:54,963
But not impossible.

444
00:35:55,753 --> 00:35:59,073
You're a big girl, Anyanka.
You understand how this works.

445
00:35:59,073 --> 00:36:01,323
The proverbial scales must balance.

446
00:36:01,553 --> 00:36:05,803
ln order to restore the lives of the victims,
the Fates require a sacrifice.

447
00:36:06,713 --> 00:36:09,163
The life and soul of a vengeance demon.

448
00:36:12,713 --> 00:36:13,963
- Do it.
- Wait!

449
00:36:14,193 --> 00:36:16,643
- Stay out of this, Xander.
- OK, right.

450
00:36:17,833 --> 00:36:20,683
That seems smart -
he just said you have to die!

451
00:36:21,633 --> 00:36:24,383
Perhaps there's some sort of alternate price?

452
00:36:25,153 --> 00:36:26,953
Xander, you can't help me.

453
00:36:30,953 --> 00:36:33,403
l'm not even sure there's a me to help.

454
00:36:37,353 --> 00:36:39,353
l understand the price. Do it.

455
00:36:41,153 --> 00:36:43,203
You're sure? This is your wish?

456
00:36:45,833 --> 00:36:47,133
This is my wish.

457
00:36:49,553 --> 00:36:50,853
Undo what l did.

458
00:36:53,193 --> 00:36:54,193
Very well.

459
00:36:55,033 --> 00:36:55,683
No!

460
00:37:01,473 --> 00:37:02,223
Anya.

461
00:37:05,393 --> 00:37:06,743
- Hallie?
- Aargh!

462
00:37:16,593 --> 00:37:20,953
Who did you think you were dealing with?
Did you think it'd be that easy to get away?

463
00:37:20,953 --> 00:37:22,103
- Why?
- Why?!

464
00:37:22,753 --> 00:37:25,453
- Because you wished it!
- But she was yours.

465
00:37:25,833 --> 00:37:27,783
The way <i>you</i> were mine?

466
00:37:28,073 --> 00:37:30,373
Haven't l taught you anything, Anya?

467
00:37:30,473 --> 00:37:33,473
Never go for the kill
when you can go for the pain.

468
00:37:33,913 --> 00:37:37,163
Hold him back, Slayer.
Wouldn't want anyone to get hurt.

469
00:37:38,593 --> 00:37:42,243
l've got plenty of girls.
There will always be vengeance demons.

470
00:37:42,633 --> 00:37:44,633
But now you, Anya, you're out.

471
00:37:45,993 --> 00:37:48,393
Congratulations. Your wish is granted.

472
00:37:48,953 --> 00:37:50,653
You should've killed me.

473
00:37:52,193 --> 00:37:54,293
Oh, l wouldn't worry about that.

474
00:37:55,193 --> 00:37:57,143
From beneath you, it devours.

475
00:37:58,153 --> 00:38:00,453
Be patient. All good things in time.

476
00:38:19,953 --> 00:38:21,803
Go. l'll check on the boys.

477
00:38:30,273 --> 00:38:31,323
Anya, wait.

478
00:38:32,873 --> 00:38:34,823
Xander, please, just go away.

479
00:38:36,793 --> 00:38:39,443
Whatever's between us... it doesn't matter.

480
00:38:41,433 --> 00:38:43,483
You shouldn't be alone in this.

481
00:38:45,193 --> 00:38:46,393
Yes, l should.

482
00:38:49,113 --> 00:38:50,413
My whole life...

483
00:38:52,153 --> 00:38:54,603
l've just clung to whatever came along.

484
00:38:56,353 --> 00:38:59,353
Well, speaking as a clingee...
l kinda didn't mind.

485
00:39:04,033 --> 00:39:05,683
Thanks. For everything.

486
00:39:24,873 --> 00:39:25,723
Xander?

487
00:39:30,793 --> 00:39:32,593
What if l'm really nobody?

488
00:39:35,313 --> 00:39:36,613
Don't be a dope.

489
00:39:38,633 --> 00:39:39,683
l'm a dope.

490
00:39:42,753 --> 00:39:43,753
Sometimes.

491
00:39:46,353 --> 00:39:47,603
That's a start.

